article.headline: East Carolina 94, St. Andrew's 58
article.story: GREENVILLE, N.C. -- James Legan scored 20 points and Darrius Morrow came off the bench to add 15 points and 10 rebounds as East Carolina dominated St. Andrew's 94-58 Sunday. St. Andrew's, a Division II school, maintained a short lead early in the first half against Division I East Carolina. Trailing 12-11, the Pirates' Brock Young hit a 3-pointer to put East Carolina (2-0) ahead for good with 12:44 left in the first half. Sam Hinnant scored 14 and Daquan Joyner chipped in 13 for the Pirates. Joseph Gripper led the Knights (0-2) with 15 points, while Taiwon Grooms added 12. East Carolina shot 52.2 percent from the field (36 of 69) compared to 34.9 percent (22 of 63) for St. Andrew's.
